":"1255–Overleden","Abt 1303":"circa 1303","1350":"1350","Abt 1301":"circa 1301","1360":"1360","1381":"1381","abt 1342":"circa 1342","abt 1335":"circa 1335","1303":"1303","1335":"1335","1379":"1379","1301":"1301","1255":"1255","1342":"1342","before 1350":"vóór 1350","1309":"1309","1329":"1329","Sweden":"Zweden","Opundo, Ostergotland, Sweden":"Östergötland, Zweden","Stockholm, Sweden":"Stockholm, Stockholm, Zweden","Sweden, Sweden":"Sweden, Sweden Township, Potter, Pennsylvania, Verenigde Staten van Amerika","of Sweden":"Zweden"},"en":{"–before 1350":"–before 1350","–1350":"–1350","–Female":"Deceased","1301–Male":"1301–Deceased","1303–1381":"1303–1381","1303–Female":"1303–Deceased","1329–1379":"1329–1379","1335–1360":"1335–1360","1342–Female":"1342–Deceased","–1379":"–1379","–1381":"–1381","–1309":"–1309","1255–Female":"1255–Deceased","Abt 1303":"about 1303","1350":"1350","Abt 1301":"about 1301","1360":"1360","1381":"1381","abt 1342":"about 1342","abt 1335":"about 1335","1303":"1303","1335":"1335","1379":"1379","1301":"1301","1255":"1255","1342":"1342","before 1350":"before 1350","1309":"1309","1329":"1329","Sweden":"Sweden","Opundo, Ostergotland, Sweden":"Östergötland, Sweden","Stockholm, Sweden":"Stockholm, Stockholm, Sweden","Sweden, Sweden":"Sweden, Sweden Township, Potter, Pennsylvania, United States","of Sweden":"Sweden","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Magnusson","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Erik, Niels, Anders, Erland, Gisli, Kerstin, Lars, Nils, Ottar, Thor.  German Hans, Kurt, Fritz.","Swedish: patronymic from the personal name   Magnus  .","Americanized form of Danish, Norwegian, or North German   Magnussen  , a cognate of 1 above."],"variants":[{"name":"Magnus","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Gerhard, Bernd, Egon, Erwin, Kurt, Otto, Reinhard, Volker, Wilhelm, Wolfgang.","German, Flemish, and Walloon: from the personal name <i>Magnus</i>, which is from the Latin adjective <i>magnus</i> ‘great’ or a Latinized form of a short form of ancient Germanic compound names based on the element <i>magan</i> ‘strength, might’. The name was borne by several early Christian saints, including St. Magnus (8th century), a monk in St. Gallen in Switzerland and missionary in Allgäu in southern Germany, whose real name was <i>Magnoald</i>. This surname is also found in France (Alsace and Lorraine). In Belgium, it may also be a Latinized (humanistic) form of Walloon   Legrand  .","English, Scottish, Swedish, Danish, Norwegian, and North German: from the Scandinavian personal name <i>Magnus</i>, borne by Magnus the Good (died 1047), king of Norway and Denmark, who was named for the Emperor Charlemagne, Latin <i>Carolus Magnus</i> ‘Charles the Great’, under the impression that <i>Magnus</i> was a personal name. The name spread from Norway to the eastern Scandinavian royal houses, and became popular all over Scandinavia and thence in the English Danelaw. It has also been adopted as a Jewish name."]},{"name":"Magnuson","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Erik, Nels, Helmer, Sven, Kerstin, Alf, Anders, Hilma, Knut, Monrad, Thor.","Americanized form (and a rare Swedish variant) of Swedish   Magnusson  .","Americanized form of Danish, Norwegian, and North German   Magnussen  , a cognate of 1 above."]},{"name":"Manson","meanings":["Scottish (mainly the Northern Isles): shortened form of   Magnusson  .","English: patronymic, probably sometimes from the Middle English personal name <i>Man</i>, <i>Manne</i> (Old English <i>Mann(a)</i> or Old Danish <i>Manni</i>) + <i>-son</i>; compare   Mann  . Occasionally perhaps from a Middle English personal name <i>Mainstan</i> (Old English <i>Mægenstān</i>, from <i>mægen</i> ‘might, power’ + <i>stān</i> ‘stone’).","Americanized form of Swedish <b>Månsson</b> (rarely <b>Månson</b>): patronymic from the personal name <i>Måns</i>, a derivative of   Magnus  . Compare   Monson  ."]}]},{"name":"Algot","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Old Norse personal name <i>Alfgautr</i>, from <i>alfr</i> ‘elf’ + <i>Gautr</i> ‘Goth’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Algot Magnusson was born as the son of Magnus Algotsson and Mrs. Magnus Algotsson. He had at least 4 sons and 4 daughters with Mektild Lydersdotter van Kyren. He died before 1350."},"et":{"–before 1350":"–enne 1350","–1350":"–1350","–Female":"Surnud","1301–Male":"1301–Surnud","1303–1381":"1303–1381","1303–Female":"1303–Surnud","1329–1379":"1329–1379","1335–1360":"1335–1360","1342–Female":"1342–Surnud","–1379":"–1379","–1381":"–1381","–1309":"–1309","1255–Female":"1255–Surnud","Abt 1303":"umbes 1303","1350":"1350","Abt 1301":"umbes 1301","1360":"1360","1381":"1381","abt 1342":"umbes 1342","abt 1335":"umbes 1335","1303":"1303","1335":"1335","1379":"1379","1301":"1301","1255":"1255","1342":"1342","before 1350":"enne 1350","1309":"1309","1329":"1329","Sweden":"Rootsi","Opundo, Ostergotland, Sweden":"Östergötland, Rootsi","Stockholm, Sweden":"Stockholm, Stockholm, Rootsi","Sweden, Sweden":"Sweden, Sweden Township, Potter, Pennsylvania, Ameerika Ühendriigid","of Sweden":"Rootsi"},"fi":{"–before 1350":"–ennen vuotta 1350","–1350":"–1350","–Female":"Kuollut","1301–Male":"1301–Kuollut","1303–1381":"1303–1381","1303–Female":"1303–Kuollut","1329–1379":"1329–1379","1335–1360":"1335–1360","1342–Female":"1342–Kuollut","–1379":"–1379","–1381":"–1381","–1309":"–1309","1255–Female":"1255–Kuollut","Abt 1303":"noin 1303","1350":"1350","Abt 1301":"noin 1301","1360":"1360","1381":"1381","abt 1342":"noin 1342","abt 1335":"noin 1335","1303":"1303","1335":"1335","1379":"1379","1301":"1301","1255":"1255","1342":"1342","before 1350":"ennen vuotta 1350","1309":"1309","1329":"1329","Sweden":"Ruotsi","Opundo, Ostergotland, Sweden":"Östergötland, Ruotsi","Stockholm, Sweden":"Stockholm, Stockholm, Ruotsi","Sw